name: app.R
content: # R PACKAGES ---- library(plyr) library(dplyr) library(tidyr) library(shiny) library(shinydashboard) library(shinyjs) library(ggplot2) library(plotly) library(scales) library(zoo) library(RColorBrewer) # DATA PROCESSING ---- full_data <- read.csv( "data/TB Monthly Stats for Dashboard.csv", stringsAsFactors = F, check.names = F ) full_data$`Time Period` <- as.Date(full_data$`Time Period`) full_data$`Herd Prevalence`[full_data$County == "Great Britain Total"] <- (full_data$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[full_data$County == "Great Britain Total"] / full_data$`Herds Registered on Sam`[full_data$County == "Great Britain Total"]) * 100 county_reference <- read.csv("data/County List.csv", stringsAsFactors = F) variables <- read.csv("data/Variable Descriptions.csv", stringsAsFactors = F) active.date <- max(full_data$`Time Period`) last.year <- seq(active.date, length.out = 2, by = "-1 year")[2] active.month <- months(active.date) active.year <- active.date plot_colours <- c("#0000C3", "#00AD00", "#E00FFF", "#206F65", "#613000") # UI DESIGN ---- ui <- dashboardPage( dashboardHeader(title = "Bovine TB Interactive Dashboard"), dashboardSidebar(sidebarMenu( menuItem("Summary Data", tabName = "summary"), menuItem("Long Term Trends", tabName = "trends"), menuItem("Headline Statistics", tabName = "headlines") )), dashboardBody( tags$style( type = "text/css", ".fa-arrow-up {color: tomato}", ".fa-arrow-down {color: springgreen}", ".fa-minus {color: orange}", ".fa-tag {color: slategrey}", ".fa-eye-dropper {color: slategrey}" ), tabItems( tabItem( tabName = "summary", fluidRow(column( width = 4, box( width = NULL, title = "Select an area to view a summary:", selectInput( inputId = "summary_region", label = "Select a Country or Risk Area:", choices = unique(county_reference$Area) ) , selectInput( inputId = "summary_county", label = "Select a County:", choices = c("England Total") ) ) ), column( width = 8, box( title = textOutput("summaryheading", inline = T), width = NULL, p( "At the end of ", format(active.year, "%B %Y"), " there were ", htmlOutput("herdvalue", inline = T), htmlOutput("nonotfvalue", inline = T), htmlOutput("nonotfchange", inline = T) ), p(strong(textOutput( "prevalencetext", inline = T ))), p( "In the 12 months up to ", format(active.year, "%B %Y"), " there were ", htmlOutput("testvalue", inline = T), htmlOutput("nhivalue", inline = T), htmlOutput("nhichange", inline = T) ), p(strong(textOutput( "incidencetext", inline = T ))) ) )), fluidRow( column( width = 4, valueBoxOutput("herdbox", width = NULL), valueBoxOutput("nonotfbox", width = NULL) ), column( width = 4, valueBoxOutput("testbox", width = NULL), valueBoxOutput("nhibox", width = NULL) ), column( width = 4, valueBoxOutput("slaughterbox", width = NULL), valueBoxOutput("slhcasebox", width = NULL) ) ) ), tabItem(tabName = "trends", fluidRow( column( width = 6, box( width = NULL, title = "Select an area to view long-term trends:", selectInput( inputId = "trend_region", label = "Select a Country or Region:", choices = unique(county_reference$Area) ), selectInput( inputId = "trend_county", label = "Select a County:", choices = c("England Total") ), selectInput( inputId = "trend_variable", label = "Select a Statistic:", choices = variables$Variable, selected = "New Herd Incidents" ) ) ), column( width = 6, box( width = NULL, title = "Select another area to compare trends:", selectInput( inputId = "comparison_region", label = "Select a Country or Region:", choices = unique(county_reference$Area) ), selectInput( inputId = "comparison_county", label = "Select a County:", choices = c("Wales Total") ), checkboxInput(inputId = "compare", label = "Check this box to enable comparison.") ) ) ), fluidRow(plotlyOutput("trendchart"))), tabItem( tabName = "headlines", fluidRow(column( width = 12, selectInput( inputId = "headline_scale", label = "Select which set of Headline Statistics you would like to view:", choices = c("Great Britain Countries", "England Risk Areas", "Wales TB Areas") ) )), fluidRow( column(width = 6, h1("Herd Incidence") , plotlyOutput("incidencechart")), column( width = 6, h1("Herd Prevalence"), plotlyOutput("prevalencechart") ) ), fluidRow( column( width = 6, h1("Total Cattle Slaughtered"), plotlyOutput("slaughterchart") ), column(width = 6, h1("Total Cattle Tests"), plotlyOutput("testchart")) ), fluidRow( column( width = 6, h1("New Herd Incidents"), tableOutput("incidentstable") ), column( width = 6, h1("Herds not officially TB-free at the end of the period"), tableOutput("nonotftable") ) ) ) ) ) ) # INTERNAL FUNCTIONS ---- server <- function(input, output, session) { # SUMMARY TAB FUNCTIONS ---- summary_counties <- reactive({ county_reference$County[county_reference$Area == input$summary_region] }) observe({ updateSelectInput( session, "summary_county", label = paste0("Select a County in ", input$summary_region, ":"), choices = summary_counties() ) }) summary_filter <- reactive({ summary_data <- full_data[full_data$County == input$summary_county, c( "Time Period", "County", "Herds Registered on Sam", "Non-OTF Herds at end of period", "Tests on OTF Herds", "Total Cattle Tests", "New Herd Incidents", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases", "Herd Incidence", "Herd Prevalence" )] summary_data[, c( "Tests on OTF Herds", "Total Cattle Tests", "New Herd Incidents", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases" )] <- rollsum(summary_data[, c( "Tests on OTF Herds", "Total Cattle Tests", "New Herd Incidents", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases" )], 12, na.pad = T, align = "right") summary_data <- summary_data[summary_data$`Time Period` %in% c(last.year, active.year),] }) clean_summary_county <- reactive({ clean_county <- gsub(" Total", "", input$summary_county) clean_county <- gsub("Risk Area", "Risk Area of England", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("Edge Area", "Edge Area of England", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("TB Area", "TB Area of Wales", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("^(.*Area of England)", "the \\1", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("^(.*Area of Wales)", "the \\1", clean_county) }) output$summaryheading <- renderText({ paste0( "Bovine TB summary for ", clean_summary_county(), " over the 12 months up to ", format(active.year, "%B %Y") ) }) output$herdvalue <- renderText({ paste0( "", prettyNum( summary_filter()$`Herds Registered on Sam`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), " cattle herds in ", clean_summary_county(), "," ) }) output$nonotfvalue <- renderText({ paste0( " of which ", prettyNum( summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), " were not officially TB-free due to a bTB incident, " ) }) output$nonotfchange <- renderText({ if (summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2] > summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[1]) { box_icon <- "arrow-up" change_text <- paste0( "an increase of ", prettyNum(round(100 * abs( 1 - ( summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2] / summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[1] ) ), 1)), "% since ", format(last.year, "%B %Y"), "." ) } if (summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2] < summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[1]) { box_icon <- "arrow-down" change_text <- paste0( "a decrease of ", prettyNum(round(100 * abs( 1 - ( summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2] / summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[1] ) ), 1)), "% since ", format(last.year, "%B %Y"), "." ) } if (summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2] == summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[1]) { box_icon <- "minus" change_text <- paste0("no change since ", format(last.year, "%B %Y"), ".") } return(change_text) }) output$testvalue <- renderText({ paste0( "", prettyNum( summary_filter()$`Tests on OTF Herds`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), " tests on officially TB-free herds in ", clean_summary_county(), "," ) }) output$nhivalue <- renderText({ paste0( " resulting in ", prettyNum( summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), " new TB breakdowns, " ) }) output$nhichange <- renderText({ if (summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2] > summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[1]) { box_icon <- "arrow-up" change_text <- paste0( "an increase of ", prettyNum(round(100 * abs( 1 - ( summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2] / summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[1] ) ), 1)), "% since the 12 months up to ", format(last.year, "%B %Y"), "." ) } if (summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2] < summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[1]) { box_icon <- "arrow-down" change_text <- paste0( "a decrease of ", prettyNum(round(100 * abs( 1 - ( summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2] / summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[1] ) ), 1)), "% since the 12 months up to ", format(last.year, "%B %Y"), "." ) } if (summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2] == summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[1]) { box_icon <- "minus" change_text <- paste0( "no change since the 12 months up to ", format(last.year, "%B %Y"), "." ) } return(change_text) }) output$prevalencetext <- renderText({ paste0( "Herd prevalence in ", clean_summary_county(), " was ", prettyNum( round(summary_filter()$`Herd Prevalence`[2], 1), drop0trailing = T ), "%" ) }) output$incidencetext <- renderText({ paste0( "Herd incidence in ", clean_summary_county(), " was ", prettyNum( round(summary_filter()$`Herd Incidence`[2], 1), drop0trailing = T ) ) }) output$herdbox <- renderValueBox({ valueBox( color = "navy", value = prettyNum( summary_filter()$`Herds Registered on Sam`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), subtitle = "Registered Herds", icon = icon("tag") ) }) output$nonotfbox <- renderValueBox({ if (summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2] > summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[1]) box_icon <- "arrow-up" if (summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2] < summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[1]) box_icon <- "arrow-down" if (summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2] == summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[1]) box_icon <- "minus" valueBox( color = "navy", value = prettyNum( summary_filter()$`Non-OTF Herds at end of period`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), subtitle = "Non-OTF Herds at end", icon = icon(box_icon) ) }) output$testbox <- renderValueBox({ valueBox( color = "navy", value = prettyNum( summary_filter()$`Total Cattle Tests`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), subtitle = "Cattle Tested", icon = icon("eye-dropper") ) }) output$nhibox <- renderValueBox({ if (summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2] > summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[1]) box_icon <- "arrow-up" if (summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2] < summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[1]) box_icon <- "arrow-down" if (summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2] == summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[1]) box_icon <- "minus" valueBox( color = "navy", value = prettyNum( summary_filter()$`New Herd Incidents`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), subtitle = "New Herd Incidents", icon = icon(box_icon) ) }) output$slaughterbox <- renderValueBox({ if (summary_filter()$`Total Cattle Slaughtered`[2] > summary_filter()$`Total Cattle Slaughtered`[1]) box_icon <- "arrow-up" if (summary_filter()$`Total Cattle Slaughtered`[2] < summary_filter()$`Total Cattle Slaughtered`[1]) box_icon <- "arrow-down" if (summary_filter()$`Total Cattle Slaughtered`[2] == summary_filter()$`Total Cattle Slaughtered`[1]) box_icon <- "minus" valueBox( color = "navy", value = prettyNum( summary_filter()$`Total Cattle Slaughtered`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), subtitle = "Cattle Slaughtered", icon = icon(box_icon) ) }) output$slhcasebox <- renderValueBox({ if (summary_filter()$`Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases`[2] > summary_filter()$`Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases`[1]) box_icon <- "arrow-up" if (summary_filter()$`Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases`[2] < summary_filter()$`Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases`[1]) box_icon <- "arrow-down" if (summary_filter()$`Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases`[2] == summary_filter()$`Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases`[1]) box_icon <- "minus" valueBox( color = "navy", value = prettyNum( summary_filter()$`Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases`[2], big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ), subtitle = "Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases", icon = icon(box_icon) ) }) # TRENDS TAB FUNCTIONS ---- trend_counties <- reactive({ county_reference$County[county_reference$Area == input$trend_region] }) observe({ updateSelectInput( session, "trend_county", label = paste0("Select a County in ", input$trend_region, ":"), choices = trend_counties() ) }) trend_filter <- reactive({ trend_data <- full_data[full_data$County == input$trend_county,] trend_data[, c( "Total Tests on Herds", "Tests on OTF Herds", "Total Cattle Tests", "New Herd Incidents", "New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Withdrawn", "New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Suspended", "New Herd Incidents Unclassified", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "TB Test Positive Cattle Slaughtered", "Inconclusive Reactors Slaughtered", "Direct Contacts Slaughtered", "Slaughterhouse Cases Reported to APHA", "Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases" )] <- rollsum(trend_data[, c( "Total Tests on Herds", "Tests on OTF Herds", "Total Cattle Tests", "New Herd Incidents", "New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Withdrawn", "New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Suspended", "New Herd Incidents Unclassified", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "TB Test Positive Cattle Slaughtered", "Inconclusive Reactors Slaughtered", "Direct Contacts Slaughtered", "Slaughterhouse Cases Reported to APHA", "Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases" )], 12, na.pad = T, align = "right") trend_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`[is.na(trend_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`)] <- (trend_data$`Herd Incidence`[is.na(trend_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`)] / trend_data$`New Herd Incidents`[is.na(trend_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`)]) * trend_data$`New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Withdrawn`[is.na(trend_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`)] trend_data$`Herd Prevalence` <- trend_data$`Herd Prevalence` / 100 trend_data }) clean_trend_county <- reactive({ clean_county <- gsub(" Total", "", input$trend_county) clean_county <- gsub("Risk Area", "Risk Area of England", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("Edge Area", "Edge Area of England", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("TB Area", "TB Area of Wales", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("^(.*Area of England)", "the \\1", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("^(.*Area of Wales)", "the \\1", clean_county) }) comparison_counties <- reactive({ county_reference$County[county_reference$Area == input$comparison_region] }) observe({ updateSelectInput( session, "comparison_county", label = paste0("Select a County in ", input$comparison_region, ":"), choices = comparison_counties() ) }) comparison_filter <- reactive({ comparison_data <- full_data[full_data$County == input$comparison_county,] comparison_data[, c( "Total Tests on Herds", "Tests on OTF Herds", "Total Cattle Tests", "New Herd Incidents", "New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Withdrawn", "New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Suspended", "New Herd Incidents Unclassified", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "TB Test Positive Cattle Slaughtered", "Inconclusive Reactors Slaughtered", "Direct Contacts Slaughtered", "Slaughterhouse Cases Reported to APHA", "Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases" )] <- rollsum(comparison_data[, c( "Total Tests on Herds", "Tests on OTF Herds", "Total Cattle Tests", "New Herd Incidents", "New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Withdrawn", "New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Suspended", "New Herd Incidents Unclassified", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "TB Test Positive Cattle Slaughtered", "Inconclusive Reactors Slaughtered", "Direct Contacts Slaughtered", "Slaughterhouse Cases Reported to APHA", "Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases" )], 12, na.pad = T, align = "right") comparison_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`[is.na(comparison_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`)] <- (comparison_data$`Herd Incidence`[is.na(comparison_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`)] / comparison_data$`New Herd Incidents`[is.na(comparison_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`)]) * comparison_data$`New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Withdrawn`[is.na(comparison_data$`Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn`)] comparison_data$`Herd Prevalence` <- comparison_data$`Herd Prevalence` / 100 comparison_data }) clean_comparison_county <- reactive({ clean_county <- gsub(" Total", "", input$comparison_county) clean_county <- gsub("Risk Area", "Risk Area of England", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("Edge Area", "Edge Area of England", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("TB Area", "TB Area of Wales", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("^(.*Area of England)", "the \\1", clean_county) clean_county <- gsub("^(.*Area of Wales)", "the \\1", clean_county) }) output$trendchart <- renderPlotly({ trend_data <- trend_filter() trend_data$County <- gsub("^the ", "", clean_trend_county()) compare_counties <- c(gsub("^the ", "", clean_trend_county())) if ((input$compare == T) && !(input$trend_county == input$comparison_county)) { comparison_data <- comparison_filter() comparison_data$County <- gsub("^the ", "", clean_comparison_county()) trend_data <- bind_rows(trend_data, comparison_data) compare_counties <- c( gsub("^the ", "", clean_trend_county()), gsub("^the ", "", clean_comparison_county()) ) } trend_data <- trend_data[!is.na(trend_data[, input$trend_variable]),] if (input$trend_variable == "Herd Prevalence") output_format <- ".1~%" else output_format <- ",.1~f" plot_ly( data = trend_data, x = trend_data$`Time Period`, y = trend_data[, input$trend_variable], color = factor(trend_data$County, levels = compare_counties), colors = plot_colours[1:(1 + input$compare)], type = "scatter", mode = "lines" ) %>% layout( xaxis = list(hoverformat = paste0( input$trend_variable, " 12 months to end %B %Y" )), yaxis = list( range = c(0, max(trend_data[, input$trend_variable], na.rm = T)), title = input$trend_variable, hoverformat = output_format, tickformat = output_format ), hovermode = "x unified", hoverlabel = list(namelength = -1), showlegend = T, legend = list( traceorder = "normal", orientation = "h", x = 0 ) ) }) # HEADLINE TAB FUNCTIONS ---- headline_filter <- reactive({ if (input$headline_scale == "Great Britain Countries") headline_data <- full_data[full_data$County %in% c("England Total", "Scotland Total", "Wales Total"), ] if (input$headline_scale == "England Risk Areas") headline_data <- full_data[full_data$County %in% c("High Risk Area Total", "Edge Area Total", "Low Risk Area Total"), ] if (input$headline_scale == "Wales TB Areas") headline_data <- full_data[full_data$County %in% c( "High East TB Area", "High West TB Area", "Intermediate Mid TB Area", "Intermediate North TB Area", "Low TB Area" ), ] headline_data <- headline_data[, c( "Time Period", "County", "Herd Incidence", "Herd Prevalence", "Total Cattle Tests", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "New Herd Incidents", "Non-OTF Herds at end of period" )] headline_data$County <- gsub(" Total", "", headline_data$County) headline_data$County <- gsub(" TB Area", "", headline_data$County) headline_data[, c("Total Cattle Tests", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "New Herd Incidents")] <- rollsum(headline_data[, c("Total Cattle Tests", "Total Cattle Slaughtered", "New Herd Incidents")], 12, na.pad = T, align = "right") headline_data }) output$incidencechart <- renderPlotly({ headline_data <- headline_filter() headline_data <- headline_data[!is.na(headline_data$`Herd Incidence`), ] plot_ly( x = headline_data$`Time Period`, y = headline_data$`Herd Incidence`, color = factor(headline_data$County, levels = unique(headline_data$County)), colors = plot_colours[1:length(unique(headline_data$County))], type = "scatter", mode = "lines" ) %>% layout( xaxis = list(hoverformat = "Herd Incidence 12 months to end %B %Y", title = ""), yaxis = list( range = c(0, max( headline_data$`Herd Incidence`, na.rm = T )), title = "Herd Incidence", hoverformat = ".1~f" ), hovermode = "x unified", hoverlabel = list(namelength = -1), showlegend = T, legend = list( traceorder = "normal", orientation = "h", x = 0 ) ) }) output$prevalencechart <- renderPlotly({ headline_data <- headline_filter() headline_data <- headline_data[!is.na(headline_data$`Herd Prevalence`), ] headline_data$`Herd Prevalence` <- headline_data$`Herd Prevalence` / 100 plot_ly( x = headline_data$`Time Period`, y = headline_data$`Herd Prevalence`, color = factor(headline_data$County, levels = unique(headline_data$County)), colors = plot_colours[1:length(unique(headline_data$County))], type = "scatter", mode = "lines" ) %>% layout( xaxis = list(hoverformat = "Herd Prevalence at end of %B %Y", title = ""), yaxis = list( range = c(0, max( headline_data$`Herd Prevalence`, na.rm = T )), title = "Herd Prevalence", hoverformat = ".1~%", tickformat = "~%" ), hovermode = "x unified", hoverlabel = list(namelength = -1), showlegend = T, legend = list( traceorder = "normal", orientation = "h", x = 0 ) ) }) output$slaughterchart <- renderPlotly({ slaughter_data <- headline_filter() relevant_dates <- seq(from = active.date, by = "-1 year", length.out = 7) slaughter_data <- slaughter_data[slaughter_data$`Time Period` %in% relevant_dates, c("Time Period", "County", "Total Cattle Slaughtered")] plot_ly( slaughter_data, x = ~ `Time Period`, y = ~ `Total Cattle Slaughtered`, color = factor(slaughter_data$County, levels = unique(slaughter_data$County)), colors = plot_colours[1:length(unique(slaughter_data$County))], type = "bar" ) %>% layout( barmode = "stack", xaxis = list( title = "12 months to end of", tickvals = ~ `Time Period`, tickformat = "%b %Y", hoverformat = "Cattle slaughtered in the 12 months up to %B %Y" ), yaxis = list( title = "Total Cattle Slaughtered", hoverformat = ",", tickformat = "~s" ), hovermode = "x unified", hoverlabel = list(namelength = -1), showlegend = T ) }) output$testchart <- renderPlotly({ test_data <- headline_filter() relevant_dates <- seq(from = active.date, by = "-1 year", length.out = 7) test_data <- test_data[test_data$`Time Period` %in% relevant_dates, c("Time Period", "County", "Total Cattle Tests")] plot_ly( test_data, x = ~ `Time Period`, y = ~ `Total Cattle Tests`, color = factor(test_data$County, levels = unique(test_data$County)), colors = plot_colours[1:length(unique(test_data$County))], type = "bar" ) %>% layout( barmode = "stack", xaxis = list( title = "12 months to end of", tickvals = ~ `Time Period`, tickformat = "%b %Y", hoverformat = "Cattle tested in the 12 months up to %B %Y" ), yaxis = list( title = "Total Cattle Tested", hoverformat = ",", tickformat = "~s" ), hovermode = "x unified", hoverlabel = list(namelength = -1), showlegend = T ) }) output$incidentstable <- renderTable({ incidents_data <- headline_filter() year_ends <- tail(unique(incidents_data$`Time Period`[months(incidents_data$`Time Period`) == "December"]), 5) last_two <- seq(from = active.date, by = "-1 year", length.out = 2) if (months(active.date) == "December") relevant_dates <- year_ends else relevant_dates <- c(year_ends[2:5], last_two) incidents_data <- incidents_data[incidents_data$`Time Period` %in% relevant_dates, c("Time Period", "County", "New Herd Incidents")] incidents_data <- pivot_wider(incidents_data, names_from = "County", values_from = "New Herd Incidents") if (months(active.date) == "December") incidents_data$`Time Period` <- format(incidents_data$`Time Period`, "%Y") else{ date_column <- c(format(incidents_data$`Time Period`[c(1,2,3,5)], "%Y"),format(incidents_data$`Time Period`[c(4,6)], "12 months to end %B %Y")) incidents_data <- incidents_data[c(1,2,3,5,4,6),] incidents_data$`Time Period` <- date_column } changes <- c("% change", 100 * ((incidents_data[nrow(incidents_data), 2:ncol(incidents_data)] / incidents_data[nrow(incidents_data) - 1, 2:ncol(incidents_data)]) - 1)) incidents_data[, 2:ncol(incidents_data)] <- sapply( incidents_data[, 2:ncol(incidents_data)], FUN = prettyNum, big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ) changes[2:length(changes)] <- sapply( changes[2:length(changes)], FUN = formatC, format = "f", digits = 1, flag = "+" ) names(changes) <- colnames(incidents_data) incidents_data <- bind_rows(incidents_data, changes) incidents_data }, align = "r") output$nonotftable <- renderTable({ nonotf_data <- headline_filter() year_ends <- tail(unique(nonotf_data$`Time Period`[months(nonotf_data$`Time Period`) == "December"]), 5) last_two <- seq(from = active.date, by = "-1 year", length.out = 2) if (months(active.date) == "December") relevant_dates <- year_ends else relevant_dates <- c(year_ends[2:5], last_two) nonotf_data <- nonotf_data[nonotf_data$`Time Period` %in% relevant_dates, c("Time Period", "County", "Non-OTF Herds at end of period")] nonotf_data <- pivot_wider(nonotf_data, names_from = "County", values_from = "Non-OTF Herds at end of period") if (months(active.date) == "December") nonotf_data$`Time Period` <- format(nonotf_data$`Time Period`, "%Y") else{ date_column <- c(format(nonotf_data$`Time Period`[c(1,2,3,5)], "%Y"),format(nonotf_data$`Time Period`[c(4,6)], "12 months to end %B %Y")) nonotf_data <- nonotf_data[c(1,2,3,5,4,6),] nonotf_data$`Time Period` <- date_column } changes <- c("% change", 100 * ((nonotf_data[nrow(nonotf_data), 2:ncol(nonotf_data)] / nonotf_data[nrow(nonotf_data) - 1, 2:ncol(nonotf_data)]) - 1)) nonotf_data[, 2:ncol(nonotf_data)] <- sapply( nonotf_data[, 2:ncol(nonotf_data)], FUN = prettyNum, big.mark = ",", drop0trailing = T ) changes[2:length(changes)] <- sapply( changes[2:length(changes)], FUN = formatC, format = "f", digits = 1, flag = "+" ) names(changes) <- colnames(nonotf_data) nonotf_data <- bind_rows(nonotf_data, changes) nonotf_data }, align = "r") } # FINAL RUN COMMAND ---- shinyApp(ui, server)

name: data/Variable Descriptions.csv
content:
Variable,Description
Herds Registered on Sam,"The number of herds registered on APHAs computer system (currently Sam, and Vetnet for years 2011 and earlier). Annual figures are recorded at the end of December of the given year. Occasionally there are changes to the number of herds registered on Sam. As well as being due to real changes in the numbers, this can be the result of routine or ad hoc data cleansing and may result in some short term fluctuations in the dataset. Country-level totals may differ from the sum of the risk areas or counties because the exact location of some herds cannot be matched to current boundaries."
Non-OTF Herds at end of period,"The number of herds which were not officially TB-free (including herds with an open breakdown with OTF status suspended or withdrawn) due to a TB incident, at the end of the time period specified."
Total Tests on Herds,The number of herds for which tuberculin skin testing is carried out on at least one animal during the period shown. Does not include Gamma tests.
Tests on OTF Herds,The number of officially TB-free (OTF) herds for which tuberculin skin testing is carried out on at least one animal during the period shown. Does not include Gamma tests.
Total Cattle Tests,The number of tests on cattle. An individual animal could be tested more than once in each time period. Includes interferon-gamma blood tests and antibody tests that have been completed. Data for Scotland does not include antibody tests.
New Herd Incidents,"The number of herds which were previously OTF but either had cattle that reacted to a tuberculin test or had a tuberculous animal disclosed by routine meat inspection at slaughter, during the period shown. Figures for Wales include incidents where OTF status has been withdrawn for epidemiological reasons only."
New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Withdrawn,"The number of new herd incidents where OTF status was withdrawn from the herd due to the detection of lesions typical of TB during post-mortem examination of one or more test reactors or inconclusive reactors, or where samples from one or more reactors, inconclusive reactors, or slaughterhouse cases produced positive culture results for Mycobacterium bovis. Figures for Wales do not include incidents where OTF status was withdrawn for epidemiological reasons only. These are currently included within the officially TB free herd status suspended figures."
New Herd Incidents with OTF Status Suspended,"The number of new herd incidents where OTF status was suspended because of reactors in the herds, but post-mortem evidence of TB was not detected. The status remains suspended until further herd tests confirm no infection remains on the farm. Figures for Wales include incidents where OTF status was withdrawn for epidemiological reasons only."
New Herd Incidents Unclassified,The number of new herd incidents where testing was still underway for reactors with post-mortem evidence of TB or a positive culture result.
Total Cattle Slaughtered,"The total number of animals slaughtered due to being TB test positive, inconclusive reactors, or direct contacts of positive animals. Prior to April 2017, some animals slaughtered as reactors or direct contacts were incorrectly classified as inconclusive reactors on Sam, and reported as such in the National and Official Statistics. These animals are now only reported under ""total animals slaughtered""."
TB Test Positive Cattle Slaughtered,"The number of animals compulsorily slaughtered because they responded to the tuberculin skin test, interferon-gamma test, or antibody test in a way that was consistent with Mycobacterium bovis infection. Will include animals that were inconclusive reactors at previous tests and tested positive at retest."
Inconclusive Reactors Slaughtered,"The number of animals showing positive reactions to bovine tuberculin that were not strong enough for the animals to be deemed reactors. However, instead of being tested again after 60 days (the normal procedure in this case) the animals were compulsorily slaughtered. This applies in certain circumstances in Wales, where some inconclusive reactors in persistent breakdown herds are automatically removed with compensation. Prior to April 2017, some animals slaughtered as reactors or direct contacts in Great Britain were incorrectly classified as inconclusive reactors on Sam, and reported as such in the National and Official Statistics. These animals are now only reported under ""total animals slaughtered""."
Direct Contacts Slaughtered,"The number of animals that, although not test reactors, were considered to have been exposed to Mycobacterium bovis and compulsorily slaughtered."
Slaughterhouse Cases Reported to APHA,The number of animals where evidence of TB infection was detected by routine meat inspection at slaughter.
Confirmed Slaughterhouse Cases,The number of slaughterhouse cases where laboratory tests have confirmed presence of Mycobacterium bovis.
Non-OTF Herds during period,"The number of herds which were not officially TB-free (including herds under movement restrictions with OTF status suspended or withdrawn) due to a TB incident, during the period shown. A herd with more than one incident in the period will be counted more than once. As herds may be under restrictions for several consecutive calendar months, the monthly figures cannot be added together to describe the total number of individual herds restricted annually."
Herds under Movement Restrictions at end of period,"The number of herds under movement restrictions at the end of the given month. This includes herds under disease restriction (as a result of confirmed or suspected disease from bTB tests or detection at slaughterhouse), herds under restriction due to an overdue test, and some movement restrictions on animals testing as inconclusive reactors pending their next test. Annual figures are recorded at the end of December of the given year. The figures may include some herds which have subsequently been dispersed or herds at premises which are not currently active."
Herd Incidence,"The number of new herd incidents per 100 herd years at risk over the time period. A herd is considered ""at risk"" for the length of time since its last negative herd test or since the end of its last breakdown. Thus this measure gives the average number of new incidents for every 100 unrestricted herds undergoing surveillance over the time period."
Herd Incidence with OTF Status Withdrawn,"The number of new herd incidents where the herd's officially TB-free status was withdrawn per 100 herd years at risk over the time period. A herd is considered ""at risk"" for the length of time since its last negative herd test or since the end of its last breakdown. Thus this measure gives the average number of new incidents where herds' officially TB-free status were withdrawn for every 100 unrestricted herds undergoing surveillance over the time period."
Herd Prevalence,The percentage of registered herds that were not officially TB-free at the end of the time period.
